The BillÂ & Melinda Gates Foundation
Trust sold 3.2 million Class B shares of  Berkshire Hathaway Inc. (BRK/A) 
to comply with federal tax rules limiting holdings by private
foundations.  The shares were sold from Nov. 14 through Jan. 12,
according to a regulatory filing today.  Berkshire Chairman and Chief Executive Officer  Warren Buffett  makes annual donations to the foundation, which works to
reduce hunger, fight disease and improve education. Class B
shares closed today at $77.77.  To contact the reporter on this story:
